               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430821-name-1242" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1242" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1242" type="surname" value="CAUDLOT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430821-name-1242" type="given" value="THEOPHILUS"></interp>THEOPHILUS CAUDLOT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a cook, and live in Chapel-street West, May-fair. About a quarter past ten o'clock in the evening of the 15th of August I was in Regent-street—I had information, and missed my handker<lb></lb>chief from my hind coat-pocket—I knew it was there a few minutes before—a person pointed out the prisoner, who was on the other side of the street—I went over, and asked if he had not got a handkerchief that did not belong to him, and, after some time, he dropped it down, and said it was not him—Skinner picked it up, and gave it me—this is it, and it is marked with my name.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> You have no doubt about it? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.</p>
